SIMPLE: epitomize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epitomize
<hw>E*pit"o*mize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Epitomized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Epitomizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
an epitome of; to shorten or abridge, as a writing or discourse; to
reduce within a smaller space; <as>as, to <ex>epitomize</ex> the works
of Justin</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To diminish, as by cutting off something; to
curtail; <as>as, to <ex>epitomize</ex> words</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epitomizer</ent>⟦br⟧
